{
  "stem": "1918.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 177.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But once she saw that it wasn't our barrack that was being selected, that we were safe in barrack 10 or 11 or 12, but it was number 13 that was being selected or so, then she came out with-- Then as she was walking with the pitcher to fetch the water from the so-called bathroom area, she would hand the pitcher over to a girl who was standing in a selected group for the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 76
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because everybody else was locked into the-- into the barracks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But the people who were selected were taken out to be taken to the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "On this occasion, they were doing that this way.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Each time they did it differently.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Selected by Mengele, and they were lined up, and then the truck would come and put them on the truck, and they would go to the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they knew that because they were the so-called Muselmanns.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A Muselmann meant that you're ready for the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Why they called us the Muselmann, I never knew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody knows to this day.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I never heard of that expression.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Viktor Frankl talks about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know why they were called Muselmanns.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the ones who could no longer walk, but shuffle.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were even thinner than I was, or the next guy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Who was evidently barely alive and was ready for the crematorium, that was-- that person was called a Muselmann.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
